DVT celebrated its 20-year anniversary at an event in Melrose Estate, Johannesburg on 16 May 2019. The event was hosted in the company’s new offices, which also house various other companies within the Dynamic Technologies group. DVT delivers a range of digital services to a wealth of clients, offering custom software development and Cloud application services as well as RPA solutions. The company’s clients include major financial players such as Standard Bank, Absa, FNB, and Nedbank, as well as communications businesses such as Vodacom. DVT CEO Dr Jaco van der Merwe said the company now employed over 500 employees, with over 1,000 staff employed across the Dynamic Technologies group. “The new building provides DVT with an outsourced custom software development delivery centre servicing local and international clients,” van der Merwe said. “In addition, the DVT Academy can now provide more classroom-based training from our on-site training facility.” The company offers specialised software design services and has offices in Johannesburg, Centurion, Durban, Cape Town, and London. The 20th anniversary celebration was hosted at the Venus Flytrap rooftop venue within the company’s new offices in Melrose Estate. Pictures of the event are posted below. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-306604" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DVT-Celebration-1.jpg" alt="DVT Celebration (1)" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DVT-Celebration-1.jpg 960w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DVT-Celebration-1-533x400.jpg 533w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DVT-Celebration-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/DVT-Celebration-1-573x430.jpg 573w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-306606" src="http